6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to museum property; defining terms;
providing that a museum may acquire title to
8 undocumented property in certain instances; providing
procedure for museums to acquire title to
9 undocumented property; providing that a museum may
acquire title to loaned property in certain
10 instances; providing procedures for museums to
acquire title to loaned property; providing procedure
11 reclamation of property in certain circumstances;
providing obligations owed to a lender by a museum;
12 providing obligations owed to a museum by a lender;
providing that a museum may apply conservation
13 measures to or dispose of property on loan to the
museum in certain circumstances; providing procedure
14 if a museum applies conservation measures to or
disposes of property; providing that a museum may
15 apply conservation measures to or dispose of
undocumented property in certain circumstances;
16 providing procedure if a museum applies conservation
measures to or disposes of undocumented property;
17 providing for limitation of legal actions against a
museum and limiting liability for a museum in certain
18 circumstances; providing that property on loan to
museum which would escheat to the state upon the
19 owners death shall instead become property of the
museum at which it is loaned to; providing for
20 codification; and providing an effective date.
