1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2001 of Title 60, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 As used in this act:
5 1. "Lender" means a person whose name appears on the records of
6 the museum as the person legally entitled to property held or on
7 loan to the museum;
8 2. "Lender's last known address" means a description of the
9 physical or mailing address of the lender, as shown on the museum's
10 records pertaining to the property on loan from the lender, which is
11 sufficient for the purpose of delivering mail;
12 3. "Loan", "loaned", and "on loan" means all deposits of
13 property with a museum which are not accompanied by a transfer of
14 title to the property;
15 4. "Museum" means an organization which uses a professional
16 staff or the equivalent, whether paid or unpaid, that is primarily
17 engaged in the acquisition, care, and exhibition to the public of
18 objects, interactive displays, or exhibits owned or used by the
19 institution. Further, a museum is understood to possess a variety
20 of the following characteristics:
21 a. is organized on a permanent or regular basis for
22 essentially educational or aesthetic purposes,
23 b. owns or uses tangible objects, either animate or
24 inanimate,
Req. No. 11602 Page 2

1 c. cares for these objects,
2 d. exhibits these objects to the general public on a
3 regular basis at or in a facility which it owns or
4 operates, and
5 e. provides educational and cultural programming;
6 5. "Person" means an individual, association, trust
7 partnership, corporation or similar organization having a legal
8 interest in property in the possession of a museum;
9 6. "Property" means all tangible objects, animate and
10 inanimate, under a museum's care which have intrinsic scientific,
11 historic, artistic, or cultural value; and
12 7. "Undocumented property" means property in the possession of
13 a museum for which the museum cannot determine the person with legal
14 interest by referencing the museum's records.
15 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2002 of Title 60, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. A museum may acquire legal title to undocumented property
19 held by a museum for seven (7) years or longer, verifiable through
20 written records, with no valid claim or contact by any person in the
21 following manner:
22 1. The museum shall publish a notice by publication in a
23 newspaper of record in the county of the museum. This notice shall
24 include:
Req. No. 11602 Page 3

1 a. brief and general description of the property,
2 b. the date or approximate date of the acquisition by the
3 museum, if known,
4 c. notice of the intent of the museum to claim title if
5 no valid claims are made within ninety (90) days from
6 the date of the first notice, and
7 d. the name and address of the museum representative to
8 contact for more information or to make a claim; and
9 2. If no valid claims have been made by the end of ninety (90)
10 days, the museum shall publish a second notice. This second notice
11 shall include:
12 a. a brief and general description of the property,
13 b. the date or approximate date of the acquisition by the
14 museum, if known,
15 c. notice that the museum claims title to the property as
16 of the date described in subparagraph c of paragraph 1
17 of this subsection, and
18 d. the name and address of the museum representative to
19 contact for more information or to make a claim.
20 B. On compliance with subsection A of this section clear and
21 unrestricted title is transferred to the museum as of the date
22 described in subparagraph c of paragraph 1 of subsection A, of this
23 section.
